text: Ana Paula Scheffer (August 18, 1989October 16, 2020) was a Brazilian individual rhythmic gymnast. She represented her nation at international competitions. She competed at world championships, including at the 2009 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships. Scheffer was discovered dead in her home in Toledo, Paraná on October 16, 2020, aged 31. == References == Category:1989 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Brazilian gymnasts Category:Sportspeople from Paraná State
